<section id="main">
<header id="nodeDecoration"><h1 id="nodeTitle">1  PROJECT PURPOSE</h1></header>
<article class="iDevice_wrapper FreeTextIdevice" id="id18">
<div class="iDevice emphasis0">
<div id="ta18_85" class="block iDevice_content">
<table width="100%" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td width="3%" valign="top">
<p class="western" align="right"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;">1 </span></span></p>
</td>
<td colspan="2" width="97%">
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="6" style="font-size: xx-large;"><b>PROJECT PURPOSE</b></span></span></p>
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;"><b>The following must be addressed: </b></span></span></p>
<ol type="a">
<li>
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;"><b>State the specific issue, problem, or need.</b></span></span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;"><b>State why the project is important and timely.</b></span></span></p>
</li>
</ol>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="3%">
<p class="western"> </p>
</td>
<td width="12%" valign="top">
<p class="western" align="right"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;">Answer: </span></span></p>
</td>
<td width="85%" valign="top">
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;">Mission Critical: Nutrition and Health. Our neighborhood is predominately Hispanic and African American. Most families are low-income, barely half are employed, and one-fourth live below poverty level with debilitating disability rates; a quarter of the adults are disabled and half of our youth are high school drop-outs. Health profiles show ravaging rates of obesity and diabetes. California¿s Department of Public Health reports that we have the state's worst heart disease and diabetes death rates. From 1997 to 2005 rates of obesity increased from 14% to 21%, higher in South LA than in other parts of the city. <br /> <br /> My Healthy City 2010 Community Data for Zip Code: 90044<br /> Total Population 107,566<br /> Age: <br /> Youth 25.48%<br /> Black / African American 33.45%<br /> Hispanic / Latino 63.45%<br /> No high school diploma 45.85% <br /> Household Incomes less than $24,999 44.37%<br /> Overweight / Obese Population 74.60%<br /> Population Age 5+ Not Consuming 5-a-day Fruits and Vegetables 57.41%<br /> <br /> Now is the Time to Act. WE CAN intends that its Urban Farm Network (UFN) Programs to provide counter-actions to these debilitating trends. The threats to our health and food security include: no access to good food; contamination of food and artificial production processes; poor eating habits; ignorance of the right foods to promote good health; lack of adequate preparation skills; and the unhealthy consequences of all of the above. The problem is the ill health of our people in low-income and under-served communities. This project will educate and empower on a local level by allowing inner-city residents, especially at-risk youth, to become actively involved in creating access to food that is fresh, locally grown, and wholesome. Urban Farm Programs will provide a network of activities designed to transform food consumers into food producers, reintegrate agriculture into the human habitat, and provide new opportunities for life-style changes and participation in revenue-producing activities. <br /> </span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
</article>
<article class="iDevice_wrapper FreeTextIdevice" id="id20">
<div class="iDevice emphasis0">
<div id="ta20_85" class="block iDevice_content">
<table width="100%" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td width="3%" valign="top">
<p class="western" align="right"></p>
</td>
<td colspan="2" width="97%">
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;"><b>Explain how project will achieve the identified program goals and objectives of the 2013 SCBGP outlined in Appendix A of the 2013 Grant Proposal Instructions. </b></span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="3%">
<p class="western"> </p>
</td>
<td width="12%" valign="top">
<p class="western" align="right"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;">Answer: </span></span></p>
</td>
<td width="85%" valign="top">
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;">Funding will allow allied organizations to meet three important goals:<br /> 1)Increase the number of micro-farm sites for community consumption and sale<br /> 2)Develop and implement a permaculture-based urban farming curricula for integration in the Youth Entrepreneurial Program<br /> 3)Build capacity to involve more local residents in food security and policy, through educational interactive events that expand awareness of how to live and eat healthily.<br /> The project employs a range of activities to: <br /> Improve food systems <br /> Formalize training <br /> Inspire food production <br /> Increase healthy food consumption<br /> Increase fresh produce access <br /> Teach food prep, cooking, storage <br /> Address health / economic concerns <br /> Give info, resources, useful action steps<br /> We anticipate a multitude of benefits that address three problems¿nutrition, health, and economics¿as involved residents restore ecological balance and harmony. Success is reinforced by the diversity of experience and commitment of each allied organization.<br /> </span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
